cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL

The paper discusses a memory model that uses unsupervised learning and sparse distributed representations, which are commonly used in neural network and machine learning research. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely categories. The paper also mentions AI and DL (Deep Learning) research, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely category. The experiments involve image and video recognition, which are common tasks in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) research.
